   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# End-to-End NLP Platform Mini-Clone\\n\",\"**NLP Project 100 of 100** — Combine ingestion, search, QA, evaluation, and tracing in one notebook.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Project Overview\\n\",\"Build a mini end-to-end NLP platform that demonstrates the full lifecycle: document ingestion → indexing → search → QA → evaluation.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in ['numpy','pandas','sentence-transformers','scikit-learn']:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg.replace('-','_'))\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','pip','install','-q',pkg])\\nprint('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, time, json, requests, re\\nfrom sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\\nfrom sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Step 1: Document Ingestion\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"class DocumentStore:\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        self.docs = []\\n        self.embeddings = None\\n        self.model = SentenceTransformer('all-MiniLM-L6-v2')\\n        self.traces = []\\n    \\n    def ingest(self, documents):\\n        self.docs = documents\\n        self.embeddings = self.model.encode(documents)\\n        self._trace('ingest', f'Ingested {len(documents)} documents')\\n        print(f'✅ Ingested {len(documents)} documents')\\n    \\n    def search(self, query, top_k=3):\\n        t0 = time.time()\\n        q_emb = self.model.encode([query])\\n        sims = cosine_similarity(q_emb, self.embeddings)[0]\\n        top_idx = sims.argsort()[-top_k:][::-1]\\n        results = [{'doc': self.docs[i], 'score': round(float(sims[i]),3)} for i in top_idx]\\n        self._trace('search', f'Query: {query[:50]}... | Time: {time.time()-t0:.3f}s')\\n        return results\\n    \\n    def answer(self, query, top_k=2):\\n        results = self.search(query, top_k)\\n        context = '\\\\n'.join(r['doc'] for r in results)\\n        prompt = f'Answer using only context. Be concise.\\\\nContext:\\\\n{context}\\\\nQuestion: {query} /no_think'\\n        try:\\n            r = requests.post('http://localhost:11434/api/generate',json={'model':'qwen3:1.7b','prompt':prompt,'stream':False},timeout=60)\\n            answer = r.json().get('response', context)\\n        except:\\n            answer = results[0]['doc']\\n        self._trace('answer', f'Q: {query[:50]}... | Answer: {answer[:80]}...')\\n        return {'answer': answer, 'sources': results}\\n    \\n    def _trace(self, step, detail):\\n        self.traces.append({'step': step, 'detail': detail, 'time': time.strftime('%H:%M:%S')})\\n\\nstore = DocumentStore()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Step 2: Ingest Documents\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"docs = [\\n    'Python is a high-level programming language created by Guido van Rossum in 1991.',\\n    'Machine learning automates pattern discovery from data using algorithms.',\\n    'Deep learning uses multi-layered neural networks for complex tasks.',\\n    'Natural language processing enables computers to understand human language.',\\n    'Transformers use self-attention to process sequences in parallel.',\\n    'BERT is a bidirectional transformer model introduced by Google in 2018.',\\n    'GPT models generate text autoregressively trained on large corpora.',\\n    'RAG retrieves relevant documents before generating answers.',\\n    'Fine-tuning adapts pre-trained models to specific tasks.',\\n    'Vector databases store embeddings for fast similarity search.',\\n]\\nstore.ingest(docs)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Step 3: Search & QA\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Search\\nresults = store.search('What is deep learning?')\\nprint('Search results:')\\nfor r in results:\\n    print(f'  [{r[\\\"score\\\"]}] {r[\\\"doc\\\"][:80]}')\\n\\n# QA\\nqa = store.answer('How does RAG work?')\\nprint(f'\\\\nQ: How does RAG work?')\\nprint(f'A: {qa[\\\"answer\\\"][:200]}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Step 4: Evaluation\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"eval_set = [\\n    {'q':'What is Python?','expected_keyword':'programming language'},\\n    {'q':'What is BERT?','expected_keyword':'transformer'},\\n    {'q':'What is RAG?','expected_keyword':'retriev'},\\n]\\n\\ncorrect = 0\\nfor e in eval_set:\\n    qa = store.answer(e['q'])\\n    hit = e['expected_keyword'].lower() in qa['answer'].lower()\\n    correct += hit\\n    status = '✅' if hit else '❌'\\n    print(f'{status} Q: {e[\\\"q\\\"]} | Expected: {e[\\\"expected_keyword\\\"]} | Found: {hit}')\\n\\nprint(f'\\\\nEval accuracy: {correct}/{len(eval_set)} = {correct/len(eval_set):.0%}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Step 5: Tracing\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"print('\\\\n📋 Execution Trace:')\\nfor t in store.traces:\\n    print(f'  [{t[\\\"time\\\"]}] {t[\\\"step\\\"]:8s} | {t[\\\"detail\\\"]}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **This mini-platform demonstrates the full NLP lifecycle** in one notebook.\\n\",\"- **Components: ingestion → embedding → search → QA → evaluation → tracing.**\\n\",\"- **Each component is modular** and can be swapped (different models, vector DBs, etc.).\\n\",\"- **For production, use frameworks like Haystack, LlamaIndex, or LangChain.**\\n\",\"- **Tracing and evaluation are often overlooked** but critical for production systems.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
    " \"metadata\":{\"kernelspec\":{\"display_name\":\"Python 3\",\"language\":\"python\",\"name\":\"python3\"},\"language_info\":{\"name\":\"python\",\"version\":\"3.11.0\"}},\n",
    " \"nbformat\":4,\"nbformat_minor\":5\n",
    "}\n"
